<HEADLINE>
OFF THE WALL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Veronica Delgado got lost on her way from her home in Chino to
the Forum in Inglewood on Sunday morning, so she showed up 40
minutes late to the 8 a.m. open call for Laker girl tryouts.
</P>
<P>
   And they wouldn't let her in the building.
</P>
<P>
   ``That kind of stinks,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
   Veronica was, in effect, locked out.
</P>
<P>
   Which means at least she has a real grasp, a concept, that
conservatively more than half of the nearly 300 dancers who showed
up knew hardly anything about.
</P>
<P>
   If they're going to be one of the 17 Laker girls this season,
they ought to know their season might consist of personal
appearances at supermarket openings and Jerry Buss's private
functions. At least keep an open calendar until December.
</P>
<P>
   ``Seriously?'' said Richelle South of Calabasas when apprised of
the NBA labor situation. The 18-year-old had just made the first
cut and was actually feeling pretty good about herself.
</P>
<P>
   ``Not just the Lakers? All of basketball?'' she continued. ``I
had no idea.''
</P>
<P>
   Candy Brown of Los Angeles said: ``Some of my boyfriends told
me, so I heard about it. But I'd bet a lot of the girls here
haven't.''
</P>
<P>
   Y'know, just don't worry about it. If you make it to the final
cut, you'll find out soon enough....
</P>
<P>
   __ Laker girl target of affection Shaq Daddy, recently kazammed
by Reebok, told the Philadelphia Daily News that he's going to
start his own shoe line next year. ``I've already got the best
designers and the best marketing group in the world lined up,''
boasted the best actor in Hollywood....
</P>
<P>
   __ The NFL has its first roster cut Tuesday, which means Dallas'
Michael Irvin (fill in your own punch line)....
</P>
<P>
   __ The News Corp. folks issued a statement recently that
ownership and control of the company won't be affected by the
pending divorce of chairman Rupert Murdoch and his future ex-wife
Anna. So that's a go for the ``Donny &AMP; Marie'' this fall....
</P>
<P>
   __ The Dodgers say it's premature to start talking about 'dozing
Dodger Stadium, despite finding out that renovation costs for 60-
to-75 luxury boxes could run about $200 million _ or about as much
as a new facility. That means they'll probably get one more
estimate by Earl Scheib then nuke the palm tree paradise this
winter....
</P>
<P>
   __ Even with the modified Stableford system, Al Davis plus
Donald Sterling in partnership to bring L.A. its most-newest NFL
franchise doesn't add up to anything positive....
</P>
<P>
   __ Those billboards that read ``Why Sundays Should Be Sooner,''
then have the San Diego Chargers helmets on them and a
season-ticket-info phone number ... sssstop, my sides are
splitting....
</P>
<P>
   __ The new name for the conference formed by the eight schools
leaving the Western Athletic Conference won't be supplied by a
corporate sponsor, as has been discussed. Utah athletic director
Chris Hill said the new group will go with ``a more conventional
name.'' Something like the ``Rebels Without A Conference.''...
</P>
<P>
   __ How Mark McGwire gets his groove back: The key is whether
batting practice pitcher Dave McKay, the Cardinals coach who was
also with the Big Bopper in Oakland, is able to throw. Since McKay
has been battling a sore back all season, sometimes to the point he
can't even stand in the first-base box, McGwire doesn't always get
his normal pregame tuneup....
</P>
<P>
   __ C'mon, Black Jack....
</P>
<P>
   __ The Mighty Ducks continue to be nickel-and-dimed by
management whose parent company decides the game is important
enough to throw $600 million in for the TV rights. Sure, that makes
cents....
</P>
<P>
   __ Campbell's commercial updates: John Elway is in as an
endorser. No soup for Reggie White....
</P>
<P>
   __ The early demise of ``The Magic Hour'' doesn't give much hope
for supporters of ``The Shawn Kemp Kiddie Korral'' show....
</P>
<P>
   __ And, please, don't think of ``The Magic Hour'' as a
painful-to-witness show that was canceled by the producers because
of nonexistent ratings. Think of it as the host who has just been
locked out.
</P>
<P>
   ((Tom Hoffarth can be reached at sptmediaaol.com))
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
