   (NYT9) HONOLULU -- Aug. 23, 1998 -- HAWAII-REPUBS-2, 8-23 --
Mayor Linda Lingle of Maui, a Republican, who is seen as the
front-runner in the race for governor of Hawaii, at a recent
candidate debate, which she did not participate in. Although Gov.
Benjamin Cayetano of Hawaii, is the latest in an unbroken line of
Democratic governors since Hawaii joined the union in 1959, the
islands' enduring sluggish economy seems to be pushing many people
beyond a point where party loyalty determines their vote. (David
Scull/New York Times Photo)
